{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"74564a46-ea2e-4374-ad0f-f855570ebe8a","content":"Use MAUI's conditional compilation with `#if` directives in `MauiProgram.cs`:\n\n```csharp\npublic static MauiApp CreateMauiApp()\n{\n    var builder = MauiApp.CreateBuilder();\n    builder.UseMauiApp<App>();\n\n#if ANDROID\n    builder.Services.AddSingleton<INotificationService, Platforms.Android.AndroidNotificationService>();\n#elif IOS\n    builder.Services.AddSingleton<INotificationService, Platforms.iOS.IosNotificationService>();\n#elif WINDOWS\n    builder.Services.AddSingleton<INotificationService, Platforms.Windows.WindowsNotificationService>();\n#endif\n\n    return builder.Build();\n}\n```\n\nEach implementation lives under `Platforms/<target>/` and is only compiled for its platform. This won't break on other platforms because the compiler excludes the irrelevant blocks entirely.\n\n**Key points:**\n- The predefined symbols (`ANDROID`, `IOS`, `WINDOWS`) are set automatically by the MAUI SDK per target framework.\n- Place each implementation in its respective `Platforms/` folder so it's only included in the correct build.\n- Inject `INotificationService` via constructor injection anywhere you need it.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"d920c1ab-6ff0-4ba5-88e7-4c7e25890a95","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about .NET MAUI dependency injection — specifically how to register platform-specific implementations of an `INotificationService` in `MauiProgram.cs`. This is a general knowledge question, not a codebase task.","outputTokens":364,"requestId":"A42C:2D0C69:2805BF:2EDEF2:69F0071F"},"id":"c1363948-71a7-49f0-8930-dc759d9bd73a","timestamp":"2026-04-28T01:02:31.371Z","parentId":"c81add6c-1a78-4eaa-8bc1-009a286fcdc7"}
